{"type":"message","id":"80a52e59","parentId":"51e04833","timestamp":"2026-02-15T11:34:41.695Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Sun 2026-02-15 13:34 GMT+2] ATOMIC ROLLBACK & SPEC-FIRST PROTOCOL.\n\n1.  **Atomic Rollback Implementation:**\n    *   Modify `agent_wrapper.py` (or create `src/deploy_safety.py`).\n    *   *Logic:*\n        1.  Snapshot current git state (commit hash).\n        2.  Apply change (simulated via file write).\n        3.  Run `/test` (pytest).\n        4.  If fail -> `git restore <file>` (or `git reset --hard`).\n        5.  Log result to `docs_archive/ROLLBACK_LOG.md`.\n\n2.  **Spec-First Protocol:**\n    *   Create `specs/` directory.\n    *   Draft `specs/buy_strategy_v1.md`:\n        *   *Goal:* Buy item if DMarket Price < 50% of Steam Price.\n        *   *Inputs:* `dmarket_price`, `steam_price`.\n        *   *Output:* Boolean `should_buy`.\n    *   *Constraint:* Must be approved by Flash before coding.\n\n3.  **Live Test (The \"Bad Code\" Scenario):**\n    *   Create `src/broken_logic.py` with syntax error (`def broken_func(: print \"error\"`).\n    *   Trigger the safety mechanism.\n    *   *Expectation:* File is created, test fails, file is deleted/reverted automatically.\n\n4.  **Output:**\n    *   Rollback Log entry.\n    *   `buy_strategy_v1.md` content.\n    *   Confirmation of system safety."}],"timestamp":1771155281693}}
{"type":"message","id":"1146ea07","parentId":"80a52e59","timestamp":"2026-02-15T11:34:53.541Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Developing the Strategy**\n\nI'm focusing on the \"Atomic Rollback & Spec-First Protocol.\" I'm starting by checking the existing directory structure to figure out file placement. Next, I'll concentrate on the \"Spec-First Protocol\" part, with the aim of creating a `specs/` directory to store specification files. I'm keen to get this protocol in motion!\n\n\n**Analyzing the Protocol's Logic**\n\nI'm starting to build a basic flow chart to represent the steps for the \"Atomic Rollback & Spec-First Protocol.\" My immediate concern is the creation of the `specs/` directory and populating it with the `buy_strategy_v1.md` file, per the specifications. I need to make sure this is done correctly before moving on.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"exec_1771155286520_410","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"dir"},"thoughtSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"write_1771155293076_411","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# Buy Strategy v1\n\n## Goal\nBuy item if DMarket Price < 50% of Steam Price.\n\n## Inputs\n- `dmarket_price` (float): Price on DMarket.\n- `steam_price` (float): Price on Steam.\n\n## Output\n- `should_buy` (boolean): True if condition met, False otherwise.\n\n## Logic\n```python\nif steam_price > 0 and dmarket_price < (steam_price * 0.5):\n    return True\nreturn False\n```\n\n## Constraints\n- Must be approved by Flash before coding.\n","file_path":"specs/buy_strategy_v1.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"write_1771155293305_412","name":"write","arguments":{"file_path":"src/deploy_safety.py","content":"import subprocess\nimport os\nimport sys\nimport datetime\n\nROLLBACK_LOG = \"docs_archive/ROLLBACK_LOG.md\"\n\ndef log_rollback(action, status, details):\n    timestamp = datetime.datetime.now().isoformat()\n    entry = f\"| {timestamp} | {action} | {status} | {details} |\\n\"\n    \n    if not os.path.exists(ROLLBACK_LOG):\n        os.makedirs(os.path.dirname(ROLLBACK_LOG), exist_ok=True)\n        with open(ROLLBACK_LOG, \"w\") as f:\n            f.write(\"| Timestamp | Action | Status | Details |\\n|---|---|---|---|\\n\")\n    \n    with open(ROLLBACK_LOG, \"a\") as f:\n        f.write(entry)\n\ndef get_git_hash():\n    try:\n        return subprocess.check_output([\"git\", \"rev-parse\", \"HEAD\"]).decode().strip()\n    except:\n        return \"unknown\"\n\ndef run_tests():\n    # Running pytest. Assuming tests are discoverable.\n    result = subprocess.run([\"pytest\"], capture_output=True, text=True)\n    return result.returncode == 0, result.stdout + result.stderr\n\ndef safe_deploy(file_path, content):\n    initial_hash = get_git_hash()\n    print(f\"Starting safe deploy. Initial Hash: {initial_hash}\")\n    \n    # 1. Snapshot state (git stash to be safe, though instructions say commit hash)\n    # For this simple script, we will rely on git restore/clean if things fail.\n    # If the file is new, we track it to remove it.\n    \n    is_new_file = not os.path.exists(file_path)\n    \n    # 2. Apply change\n    os.makedirs(os.path.dirname(file_path), exist_ok=True)\n    with open(file_path, \"w\") as f:\n        f.write(content)\n        \n    print(f\"Applied changes to {file_path}\")\n\n    # 3. Run tests\n    print(\"Running tests...\")\n    success, output = run_tests()\n    \n    if success:\n        print(\"Tests passed. Change accepted.\")\n        log_rollback(f\"Deploy {file_path}\", \"SUCCESS\", \"Tests passed\")\n        # In a real scenario, we might commit here.\n    else:\n        print(\"Tests failed! Initiating rollback...\")\n        print(output) # Debug\n        \n        # 4. Rollback\n        if is_new_file:\n            os.remove(file_path)\n            print(f\"Rollback: Deleted new file {file_path}\")\n        else:\n            subprocess.run([\"git\", \"restore\", file_path])\n            print(f\"Rollback: Restored {file_path}\")\n            \n        log_rollback(f\"Deploy {file_path}\", \"ROLLBACK\", \"Tests failed\")\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    # CLI usage: python src/deploy_safety.py <file_path> <content_string_or_file>\n    # For the test scenario, we will hardcode the broken logic test here if run directly without args,\n    # or accept args.\n    \n    if len(sys.argv) > 2:\n        path = sys.argv[1]\n        content = sys.argv[2]\n        safe_deploy(path, content)\n    else:\n        # Default test mode for the task\n        print(\"Running internal test scenario: 'Bad Code'...\")\n        broken_code = 'def broken_func(: print \"error\"' # Syntax error\n        safe_deploy(\"src/broken_logic.py\", broken_code)\n"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"exec_1771155293411_413","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python src/deploy_safety.py"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771155293531_414","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"docs_archive/ROLLBACK_LOG.md"}}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":5156,"output":1158,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":6314,"cost":{"input":0.010312,"output":0.013896,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.024208}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771155281695}}
