{"type":"message","id":"8db13d35","parentId":"942e2424","timestamp":"2026-02-15T11:35:27.525Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Analyzing Slowdown Origins**\n\nI'm now zeroing in on the cause of the delay. The `tide-bloom` process has been chugging along for a while. The `git rev-parse HEAD` call within a subprocess seems like the likely culprit, given the timing. It's time to investigate how long that specific command is taking.\n\n\n**Debugging Test Delays**\n\nI'm now investigating potential causes for the continued delay, now at 25 seconds. The suspected culprit, `subprocess.check_output([\"git\", \"rev-parse\", \"HEAD\"])`, is still the focus. I'm exploring whether the working directory is a git repo, since that command will hang otherwise. I'm also considering if `pytest`, which runs on the entire workspace, is taking a significant amount of time to discover tests. To get a better sense of progress, I'll attempt a separate `git status` check, and revisit the script's output logs.\n\n\n**Evaluating Continued Stalling**\n\nThe `tide-bloom` process is still taking a while, now at 25 seconds and counting. I've re-evaluated the `subprocess.check_output([\"git\", \"rev-parse\", \"HEAD\"])` call, suspecting a hang if not a git repo, or git needing a credential. Running `git status` will confirm the git repo status. The `pytest` execution, running across the whole directory, also appears to be another reason for the continued delay.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"exec_1771155327404_417","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"git status"},"thoughtSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"process_1771155327524_418","name":"process","arguments":{"sessionId":"tide-bloom","action":"log","limit":100}}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":8107,"output":450,"cacheRead":5395,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":8557,"cost":{"input":0.016214,"output":0.0054,"cacheRead":0.001079,"cacheWr